  "text": "We have seen that we can convert chemical reactions to ODEs. Therefore, a mapping from a stochastic process algebra to chemical reactions, which we study in this section, induces in two steps a mapping from that process algebra to ODEs. A two-step approach is desirable, because a direct mapping from a process algebra to ODEs, although possible and intuitively understandable, is more challenging [CITATION_1] [6]. The first step, from process algebra to chemical reactions, has the effect of identifying the transitions that the system performs, and the second step, from chemical reactions to ODEs, identifies the rate of change of populations of processes.",
